(46596, '4743C0AF-E4D4-4001-950E-DF85B5FA213A', '￼Part 2. A song about growing (older), climber inspiration, love, and a dash of resilience and the slow, crooked path toward healing.    Time  I move you slower I’ve got more behind me than ahead  Divide  in seconds  into sections  Plan the days of action  We are the heroes In our home movie  we the play parts In epic journeys  Interconnecting  Animating  No words  work But we only have words  We call it love  When the heart breaks  break it open  Wake up Can I believe again tonight? It comes and goes  It comes and goes You Ask  me to share  Something nobody else knows  To these 50 strangers in our house Hungry to believe and be believed in  We light it up We dive right in Dance the cha cha slide The warmest place next to the sun  Thank you for this gift  erase the distance  Souls aren’t saved at scale They need love  They need lice  the healing is slow Every body a scar Every syllable scalpel  But by now you have to know I’m half the hero With Limitless Potential  To break  open', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2022-04-04T22:17:12.620264'),
